data.title: 9705 Drummen
data.meta_description: Drummen Discovery and designation Discovered by C. J. van Houten and I. van Houten Groeneveld on plates taken by T. Gehrels. Discovery site Palomar Schmidt Discovery date
data.text:
9705 Drummen (3137 T-3) is a main-belt asteroid discovered on October 16, 1977 by C. J. van Houten and I. van Houten-Groeneveld on Palomar Schmidt plates taken by T. Gehrels.

It is named after Mat Drummen (1945-), former manager of 'Stichting de Koepel' in Utrecht (a Dutch institute for the popularisation of astronomy) and author of the 'Sterrengids', a Dutch astronomy year book.
